<h1 class="Article-title">Panel</h1>
<p class="c-Text--lead">Create layout boxes with different styles</p>

<hr>

<h2 id="section:usage"><a href="#section:usage" class="c-Text--resetLink">Usage</a></h2>

<div class="c-example">
  <div class="o-flex-grid o-flex-grid--gutters@lg o-flex-grid--1of3">
    <div class="o-flex-grid__cell">
      <div class="c-panel">
        <span class="c-badge c-badge--danger c-panel__badge">+3</span>
        <h3 class="c-panel__title">Panel title</h3>
        <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit. Deleniti eius eligendi, esse.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<p><strong class="c-badge">Note</strong> By default, a panel is blank and has no styling. Use the modifiers to alter its appearance. Like with the <code>.c-panel--box</code> below.</p>
<div class="c-code c-code--html">
<pre><code class="html">&lt;div class=&quot;c-panel&quot;&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;c-badge c-badge--danger c-panel__badge&quot;&gt;+3&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;h3 class=&quot;c-panel__title&quot;&gt;c-panel title&lt;/h3&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit. Deleniti eius eligendi, esse.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
</div>

<h3>Panel box (.c-panel--box)</h3>

<div class="c-example">
  <div class="o-flex-grid o-flex-grid--gutters@lg o-flex-grid--1of3">
    <div class="o-flex-grid__cell">
      <div class="c-panel c-panel--box">
        <span class="c-badge c-badge--danger c-panel__badge">+3</span>
        <h3 class="c-panel__title">{{ icon("trophy") }} This is the panel title</h3>
        <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <article class="o-flex-grid__cell">
      <div class="c-panel c-panel--box">
        <span class="c-badge c-badge--success c-panel__badge">Up</span>
        <h3 class="c-panel__title">{{ icon("envelope") }} This is the second panel title</h3>
        <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit. Deleniti eius eligendi, esse.</p>
      </div>
    </article>
    <section class="o-flex-grid__cell">
      <div class="c-panel c-panel--box">
        <span class="c-badge c-badge--danger c-panel__badge">+3</span>
        <h3 class="c-panel__title">{{ icon("tag") }} Third panel title</h3>
        <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit. Deleniti eius eligendi, esse consectetur adipisicing elit.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="c-code c-code--html">
  <pre><code class="html">&lt;div class=&quot;c-panel c-panel--box&quot;&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
</div>

<h3>Stacked panels (<code>.c-panel--stacked</code>)</h3>
<p>It is possible to make a panel box look as though it is stack on top of others. Useful for tabs and such like.</p>
<p><strong class="c-badge">Note</strong> This class musts be used in conjuction with <code>.c-panel--box</code>.</p>

<div class="c-example">
  <div class="c-panel c-panel--box c-panel--stacked">
    <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit. Error illum magnam minima placeat rem! Ab at beatae culpa deleniti excepturi, exercitationem illo laboriosam nostrum officia perspiciatis recusandae sequi tempora voluptates.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="c-code"><pre><code class="html">&lt;div class=&quot;c-panel c-panel--box c-panel--stacked&quot;&gt;
  ....
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre></div>

<h3>Piled panels (<code>.c-panel--piled</code>)</h3>
<p>It is possible to make a panel box look as though it is on top of a pile of others.</p>
<p><strong class="c-badge">Note</strong> This class musts be used in conjuction with <code>.c-panel--box</code>.</p>

<div class="c-example">
  <div class="c-panel c-panel--box c-panel--piled">
    <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit. Error illum magnam minima placeat rem! Ab at beatae culpa deleniti excepturi, exercitationem illo laboriosam nostrum officia perspiciatis recusandae sequi tempora voluptates.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="c-code"><pre><code class="html">&lt;div class=&quot;c-panel c-panel--box c-panel--piled&quot;&gt;
  ....
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre></div>

<h3>Attached panel (<code>.c-panel--attached</code>)</h3>
<p>It is possible to attached the panel to other attachable items, for example, the menu (in tabular format) component, to create a tab like component.</p>

<div class="c-example">
  <ul class="c-menu c-menu--tabular c-menu--attached">
    <li class="c-menu__item is-active"><a href="#" class="c-menu__link">One</a></li>
    <li class="c-menu__item"><a href="#" class="c-menu__link">Two</a></li>
    <li class="c-menu__item"><a href="#" class="c-menu__link">Three</a></li>
  </ul>
  <div class="c-panel c-panel--box c-panel--attached c-panel--stacked">
    <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit. Error illum magnam minima placeat rem! Ab at beatae culpa deleniti excepturi, exercitationem illo laboriosam nostrum officia perspiciatis recusandae sequi tempora voluptates.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="c-code"><pre><code class="html">&lt;ul class=&quot;c-menu c-menu--tabular c-menu--attached&quot;&gt;
  &lt;li class=&quot;c-menu__item is-active&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; class=&quot;c-menu__link&quot;&gt;One&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
  ....
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;c-panel c-panel--box c-panel--attached&quot;&gt;
  ....
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre></div>

<h3>Panel groups (.Panels)</h3>
<p>If you wrap you panels with a parent element with the class <code>Panels</code>, the margin is removed from the individual panel components, creating a connected look.</p>

<div class="c-example">
  <div class="Panels">
    <div class="c-panel c-panel--box">
      <p>Top panel</p>
    </div>
    <div class="c-panel c-panel--box">
      <p>Middle panel</p>
    </div>
    <div class="c-panel c-panel--box">
      <p>Bottom panel</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="c-code c-code--html">
  <pre><code class="html">&lt;div class=&quot;Panels&quot;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;c-panel c-panel--box&quot;&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Top panel&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;c-panel c-panel--box&quot;&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Middle panel&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;c-panel c-panel--box&quot;&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Bottom panel&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
</div>

